  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Building Collaborative Governance in Times of Uncertainty\" is a significant scholarly work that explores the dynamics of governance amidst unpredictable challenges. Although it has not yet received citations, the book's potential for influencing both academic scholarship and practical policy discussions is noteworthy, backed by its connections to commercial platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Leuven University Press in 2023, \"Building Collaborative Governance in Times of Uncertainty\" tackles a pressing topic in the current socio-political climate. The lack of citations at this stage suggests that the book is in its early uptake phase; however, its association with commercial platforms implies an interest from a broader audience eager to engage with its ideas.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The inferred roles of the book indicate a strong potential for scholarly uptake, with a notable strength of 0.6. This positioning signals a foundational contribution to the interdisciplinary discussion surrounding collaborative governance. Additionally, the work's relevance to sustainability and policy is marked with a strength of 0.55, suggesting that it aligns with important global agendas, such as those outlined by the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the book does not currently have any mentions in high-fidelity social or community discourse, its commercial visibility can foster future discussions. The connections to platforms like Amazon and Goodreads may enhance engagement and lead to a broader discourse in both academic and public arenas over time.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, \"Building Collaborative Governance in Times of Uncertainty\" represents a crucial entry point into understanding governance challenges today. Although it has yet to gain traction in terms of citations and community discussions, its alignment with significant commercial platforms indicates potential for future influence and engagement in both scholarly and policy-making circles.</p>",
